cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses access control mechanisms for a medical records system, which involves sensitive personal information. This suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves database design and implementation, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The healthcare domain is a major focus of the paper, indicating that it may also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
